 Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin and uncertain derivation (possibly a diminutive of a word meaning ‘rock’). It was introduced into England by  Breton  followers of  William the Conqueror , most notably  Alan , Earl of Brittany, who was rewarded for his services with vast estates in the newly conquered kingdom. In Britain the variants  <b>Allan</b>  and  <b>Allen</b>  are considerably less frequent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alan FitzRoald de Richmond was born about 1130, in Richmond, Yorkshire, England, his father, Sir Roald \"Le Ennase\" Fitz Harscoit 2nd Constable of Richmond Castle, was 38 and his mother, Garsiena FitzEnisan de Pleven, was 31. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Olivia de Croft. He died in 1201, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 72."},"et":{"about 1130–1201":"umbes 1130–1201","1123–Female":"1123–Surnud","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1128–Male":"1128–Surnud","1129–1178":"1129–1178","1129–Male":"1129–Surnud","1130–1201":"1130–1201","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1093–Male":"1093–Surnud","1100–1150":"1100–1150","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"enne 1158","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1093":"1093","1129":"1129","1128":"1128","1226":"1226","1158":"1158","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1178":"1178","1123":"1123","Abt 1165":"umbes 1165","1100":"1100","about 1130":"umbes 1130","1219":"1219","Easby, Yorkshire, England":"Easby, Yorkshire, England","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Richmond Castle, Yorkshire, England":"Richmond, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Richmond, Yorkshire, England":"Richmond, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1130–1201":"noin 1130–1201","1123–Female":"1